## Repository Layout

```
ai-agents-workshop/
├── docs/                          # Workshop content (Jekyll / just-the-docs)
│   ├── 00_setup/
│   ├── 01_chat_app_scaffold/
│   ├── 02_products_mcp_server/
│   ├── 03_products_foundry_agent/
│   ├── 04_marketing_mcp_server/
│   ├── 05_marketing_foundry_agent/
│   ├── 06_hr_foundry_iq_agent/
│   ├── 07_orchestrator_agent_framework/
│   ├── 08_response_generator_and_observability/
│   └── 09_cleanup/
├── src/                           # STARTER scaffolds — fill in as you go
│   ├── common/                    # Shared settings, Foundry client, observability
│   ├── mcp_servers/products/      # FastMCP server stub + Dockerfile + seed
│   ├── mcp_servers/marketing/     # FastMCP server stub + Dockerfile + seed
│   ├── foundry_agents/            # Stub scripts to create the 4 Foundry agents
│   ├── orchestrator/              # Magentic orchestrator stub
│   ├── app/                       # FastAPI chat UI + CLI (runnable from Ex01)
│   └── knowledge_seed/hr/         # HR Markdown for Foundry IQ
├── solution/                      # COMPLETE reference implementation
│   ├── common/  mcp_servers/  foundry_agents/  orchestrator/  app/  knowledge_seed/
│   └── docs_original/             # Original (pre-rewrite) docs for comparison
├── tests/                         # Smoke tests
├── .env.sample
├── pyproject.toml
└── README.md
```

The `src/` tree is what you edit. If you get stuck, peek at the matching
file under `solution/` — every TODO in `src/` has a working twin there.

